stories.title: West Indies make written complaint over Rajkot result
stories.summary: More than a week after India were 'awarded' the third one day in their current seven-game series with the West Indies, and the multitudes of protesting voices in the Caribbean, the West Indies Cricket Board (WICB) has written to the International

stories.title: ICC seeks security assurances from Board of Control for Cricket in India
stories.summary: The ICC today confirmed that it was seeking urgent confirmation from the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) concerning the adequacy of safety and security measures in place for the remaining four matches of the One Day International series

stories.title: Crowd trouble mars India's win at Rajkot
stories.summary: Five hundred runs scored in 77.1 overs, one explosive hundred, four other scores over 70, as many as 56 boundaries and seven sixes struck
